a:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-2","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-8 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/foldable-iphones-12gb-ram-samsungs-price-power-pla/main.jpg","alt":"Foldable iPhone’s 12GB RAM: Samsung’s Price Power Play","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 article-prose max-w-none","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":["The foldable iPhone’s arrival was always going to be a spectacle, but its 12GB RAM—supplied exclusively by Samsung—is the first concrete sign that Apple’s supply chain is bending under pressure. ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.thebell.co.kr","children":"The Bell"}]," reports that Samsung has locked in a deal to ship LPDDR5X modules starting Q2, with prices for the same 12GB configuration (already used in the ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.apple.com/iphone-17-pro/","children":"iPhone 17 Pro"}],") jumping from ~$30 to ~$70 in under a year. That’s not inflation; it’s AI’s shadow.\nMemory shortages, once a niche concern, are now a boardroom problem. The culprit? Data centers hoarding DRAM for AI workloads, leaving smartphone makers to compete for scraps. Apple, famously allergic to single-supplier dependence, is reportedly ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.macrumors.com/2024/03/15/apple-samsung-foldable-iphone-ram/","children":"increasing its reliance on Samsung"}],"—a tacit admission that its usual playbook (splitting orders between SK Hynix, Micron, and Samsung) isn’t cutting it. For Samsung, this is a masterclass in negotiation: tighter supply + Apple’s urgency = a 130% price hike on what’s essentially the same hardware.\nThe irony? Foldable phones were supposed to be the next big thing, but their success now hinges on whether Apple can stomach paying premium prices for components that, until recently, were commoditized. And users? They’ll foot the bill, one way or another."]}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"className":"not-prose my-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":[null,["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-4 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/foldable-iphones-12gb-ram-samsungs-price-power-pla/subtitle.jpg","alt":"When memory becomes a luxury, who pays the bill?","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-text-secondary italic text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium","children":"When memory becomes a luxury, who pays the bill?"}]]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Here’s what changes—and what doesn’t. ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"For users"}],", 12GB of RAM in a foldable iPhone is overkill for 90% of tasks. Even the ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.apple.com/iphone-17-pro/specs/","children":"iPhone 17 Pro"}]," ships with the same configuration, and its real-world performance gains over 8GB models are marginal for most apps. The foldable’s multitasking might shine with split-screen apps or AR, but unless you’re editing 4K video on a 7-inch screen, the extra RAM is future-proofing, not necessity.\n",["$","strong",null,{"children":"For the industry"}],", this is a stress test. Samsung’s price hike isn’t just about RAM; it’s a signal that memory is now a strategic resource, not a line item. Competitors like ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://store.google.com/product/pixel_fold","children":"Google’s Pixel Fold"}]," and ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.samsung.com/global/galaxy/galaxy-z-fold6/","children":"Samsung’s own Galaxy Z Fold 6"}]," will face the same squeeze. The difference? Apple’s margins let it absorb costs—others may cut corners (or features) instead.\nThe bigger question: Is this a one-off supply crunch or the new normal? AI’s appetite for memory isn’t slowing down, and neither is Apple’s ambition. If foldables become mainstream, we’re looking at a world where premium phones cost more not because of innovation, but because the parts do. And that’s a problem no amount of marketing can fold away."]}]]}]
